<h2>The weather in November 2018</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
Average temperatures were above the 1981-2010 average in large parts of the continent especially in the far North as well as in some Mediterranean countries. The northern part of Scandinavia and Italy had above average minimum temperatures (Figures 8 and 9). Figure 10 and 11 show that the eastern part of Europe experienced both exceptionally high temperatures at the warmest day and below or much below average temperatures during the coldest night.
